    <item>
      <title>Digital History and the Digital Modern</title>
      <link>https://www.jamessmithies.org/blog/2019/02/25/digital-history-and-digital-modern/</link>
      <pubDate>Mon, 25 Feb 2019 20:25:31 +0000</pubDate>
      <guid>https://www.jamessmithies.org/blog/2019/02/25/digital-history-and-digital-modern/</guid>
      <description>&lt;p style=&#34;text-align:center&#34;&gt;&lt;iframe frameborder=&#34;0&#34; height=&#34;389&#34; src=&#34;https://docs.google.com/presentation/d/e/2PACX-1vRhXJ5mmjhAafkSeM7wMhqJwlU2irRxelusRmRHOaVIWEocVV_9k3gaJuP-KQEwov7uS2tv2CbSXqyr/embed?start=false&amp;amp;loop=false&amp;amp;delayms=3000&#34; width=&#34;640&#34;&gt;&lt;/iframe&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&#xD;&#xA;&lt;h1 style=&#34;text-align:center&#34;&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;font-size:16pt&#34;&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;font-family:&amp;quot;Calibri Light&amp;quot;,serif&#34;&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;color:#2f5496&#34;&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;color:#000000&#34;&gt;Digital History and the Digital Modern&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/h1&gt;&#xD;&#xA;&lt;p style=&#34;text-align:center&#34;&gt;Center for Digital History Aarhus (CEDHAR) Launch Keynote&lt;/p&gt;&#xD;&#xA;&lt;p style=&#34;text-align:center&#34;&gt;22 February, 2019&lt;/p&gt;&#xD;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;color:#e74c3c&#34;&gt;&lt;em&gt;This talk was an early attempt to explore ideas that I&amp;#39;ve been pondering for some time. I&amp;#39;m conscious some areas need work. My intention is to expand it to include work by R. G. Collingwood and other writers, along with a brief history of digital history, and to provide more precision when discussing probabilistic methods.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</description>
